  "prompt": "If my ATM card is blocked for online transactions then how do i restart it?",
  "response": "If your ATM card is blocked for online transactions, you can usually proceed with the following steps to unblock it:\n\n1. **Contact Your Bank**: The first step is to call the customer service number of your bank. This number is typically found on the bank's website, your bank statements, or on the back of your card. \n\n2. **Verification**: Be prepared to verify your identity. This may involve providing personal details such as your full name, account number, date of birth, and possibly answering security questions.\n\n3. **Request Unblocking**: Once your identity is verified, inform the customer service representative about the specific issue (i.e., that your ATM card is blocked for online transactions) and request to have it unblocked.\n\n4. **Online Banking**: If you're registered for online banking, you might also log into your account and check if there\u2019s an option to unblock your card. Some banks provide this functionality through their online portals or mobile apps.\n\n5. **ATM Options**: Visit an ATM of your bank (if applicable) and see if the option to unblock online transactions is available through the ATM interface.\n\n6. **Follow Instructions**: If there are specific instructions given by the bank representative, make sure to follow them carefully.\n\n7. **Wait Time**: After your card has been unblocked, ensure that you allow some time for the changes to take effect before you attempt to use your card for online transactions.\n\nIf you do not receive assistance through the contact methods mentioned, visiting a local branch of your bank for in-person help may also be beneficial.",
